    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-11-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-11-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1058"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1058">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.112 Er 4/4.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister in temporary charge
                            of the Embassy at Constantinople</gloss> to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-11-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 29, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The contents of Department’s telegram of November 1, 1910, was brought to the
                    attention of the Ottoman Government. Strong protest was made in regard to the
                    arrest of Erickson at Monastir, and the Government promised immediate
                    investigation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carter.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
